bDdALipF3ynWPVTLxH190SVZz3hXdBSyiyUV_qE_MsqO3g ] and what it means for Amer=
ica and space, is where I think we can have the biggest impact. The world c=
ontinues to get crazier [ https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkN1qxCAQhZ8m=
3jU4aoy58GKh7GsEo7NZ2UTFmIb06Ws30ML8wAxnDvNZU3CO-dQpboX8lrGcCXXAY1uwFMxk3zC=
P3mmQTPFODMRp4UB1ivhtfGTE1fhFl7wjSfu0eGuKj-GtoJR15Kk54wNY6QY3KWG44eCs7AUIyy=
wIOly-Znceg0WNX5jPGJAs-llK2hp-a9i9xnEcbYhlitmHubWxjlJNG9cU9-Dq8MNm8302_F5Fn=
wfxmlHGqAAA1gnat6x99EIpPkhwk-0MxVZASCdw0wi6zqzd9mkrxr7q-ZVk_WdX16-nWXF5L-qj=
Y-3rHnw5RwxmWtBdDMqF8k1lnDFgrojdaEoFKAapQPaKg7h-rpA6GIBJ2ZHq7GJVhX_TH7FpisU=
 ], and I want people to meet all of the change with curiosity and optimism=
 instead of cynicism and fear.=C2=A0=C2=A0
But I=E2=80=99m more curious than smart, and I=E2=80=99m probably a little =
too optimistic.=C2=A0
So I want to hire two people to the team who are:=C2=A0
Up-and-coming experts in their fields,=C2=A0
Much more technical than I am, and=C2=A0
Know how to write well.=C2=A0
I realize that we=E2=80=99re looking for needles in a haystack, people who =
have a lot of amazing options, and in return, I=E2=80=99m hoping that I can=
 offer them space to explore broadly, a platform, and a chance to hone thei=
r storytelling skills. Technical people who can tell a compelling story are=
 hard to beat.=C2=A0
The Atoms Research Analyst will be someone who loves reading (and writing) =
research papers and doing science in the physical world. They might special=
ize in Climate, Space, Biotech, or some other corner of Deep Tech, but abov=
e all else, I want them to have a passion for, and familiarity with, everyt=
hing going on at the frontier, and an ability to explain those things to no=
rmal people, like me. They=E2=80=99ll help source and analyze deep tech inv=
estments, write company memos, and write research reports that go out to al=
l of you.=C2=A0
The Bits Research Analyst will be someone who thinks at the speed of the in=
ternet and understands all of the latest, wildest things happening in web3.=
 They can see a pile of Legos and make an educated guess as to how they mig=
ht snap together. They=E2=80=99re ideally technical, or technical enough to=
 be dangerous, familiar with the most interesting people and projects in we=
b3, and able to explain complex concepts simply and engagingly. They=E2=80=
=99ll help source and analyze web3 investments, live in Discords and Telegr=
ams, write project memos, and put together research reports that go out to =
all of you.=C2=A0
In both cases, I want people who share my optimism, but who are willing to =
tell me when I=E2=80=99m being more optimistic than the science or vibes su=
ggest I should be.=C2=A0
We=E2=80=99re open to interns, fellows, x-in-residences, part-time analysts=
, or full-time analysts, local in NYC or remote, pseudonymous or doxxed. Th=
ose titles are written in pencil; we can specialize and expand. If building=
 a Liquid Super Team [ https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkE2OhCAQRk_T7No=
AAuKCxWzmGgahWkkrECzHePuhNZlJ-EmofPWo5yzClMppctqQfI4BzwwmwrEtgAiF7BuUIXjDFN=
etFD3xRnimpSZhG14FYLVhMVh2IHkfl-AshhSvBKVcktnYVo6qRl4SJOuc6KxVWgghme0o9-PNt=
bsPEB0Y-IFypghkMTNi3h7t14N_13UcRxMTjqmEODUu1adcN87wdCllKBf5CS7FtJ5PEgynnFPB=
GONS0K7hzasTWre9Yn500lJoBIv5ZK19CLpOvNn2cUPr3rX7Sor5o9Xye7YrLFehzjnUe91jwHO=
AaMcF_K0Ab5OXlGGC-PkU-MFi9Sd6pZnqdMvEPXJ1JFnPuFKSVLJPNRX_ob_aKotC ] means b=
eing able to bring people we otherwise couldn=E2=80=99t onboard, I=E2=80=99=
m all for it. I just want the best and brightest. We=E2=80=99ll expand to m=
ore positions over time as people specialize.=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0
Hell, if there=E2=80=99s a different role that you think we should be hirin=
g for instead of these roles and aren=E2=80=99t, hijack the application and=
 let us know.=C2=A0
I just want Not Boring to be known as a place where really smart people can=
 come to both learn and teach, for as little as one newsletter or as long a=
s a career. I want it to be cross-disciplinary =E2=80=93 I think that some =
of the greatest opportunities will come at the intersection of Bits and Ato=
ms, and I hope that we can both discover and generate the coolest things ha=
ppening at those intersections. Above all else, I want it to be fun, an opp=
ortunity for high-horsepower people to relax, explore, dream, and translate=
 what they find to our audience.=C2=A0
You can find job descriptions and applications here [ https://email.mg2.sub=
stack.com/c/eJxFUV2L3SAQ_TXXtwQ1GvXBh7Z0YaEsfWlfgx-Te2UTDWbSkn9f9wa2IOPgmcP=
xnAkO4V7qabeyI_koE54b2Ax_9wUQoZJjhzqlaNnI9SCFIdGKyLTUJO3TXAFWlxaL9QCyHX5JwW=
Eq-cmglEvysJJr4digFIMR5tH4mUmtqB_iDLP0cOm6IybIASz8gXqWDGSxD8Rtvw1fbvylnVzQl=
5ryPbgtoVv69tCk-j0hNPitYPf1iXffroHux8_u1xabx-71d_f26an7HtMHswtcGgOGBxMHIal3=
ILhUrdVaKFCSJMsp51QwxrgUVPW8n5XQejAjiz5IR6EXLG8nG9xN0PXO-_3wO7rw3oeykmo_P93=
g94dbYXkCLaqp3euRE54TZOcXiFeKeC3jmet0hwy1GYiTw7YCYUbNRqUHJq7UWsySGcbHUZKmHE=
tj5f-i_wAqw6Cg ]. Be warned: applicants are going to have to write: 1,000 w=
ords on the most fascinating company or trend in their space.
Onward and Weirdward and Funward
After two years, it=E2=80=99s time for Not Boring to grow. Instead of more =
people making it more corporate and stuffy, I hope that adding new brains t=
o the mix is going to make Not Boring even weirder and more fun.=C2=A0
If you=E2=80=99re reading this, thank you for making the past two years the=
 best two years of my life and career. I feel very lucky to get to do this =
as my job. Now that we=E2=80=99re growing, please please please give us fee=
dback, tell us when we=E2=80=99re moving in the wrong direction, and point =
us towards the things that you want to learn more about.=C2=A0
All of this is only possible because you=E2=80=99re willing to read thousan=
ds of optimistic words per week. I hope that growing the team means even mo=
re reasons for optimism.
